## `test_rename_overwrites_existing_file(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-rename-4 -->

### Purpose
POSIX rename overwrites an existing destination if it is a regular file. The old destination inode is gone (nlink decremented; GC'd if nlink was 1).

### Postconditions

```python
fd = as_root.create("/a"); as_root.write(fd, b"source", offset=0); as_root.close_fd(fd)
fd = as_root.create("/b"); as_root.write(fd, b"target", offset=0); as_root.close_fd(fd)

inode_a = as_root.stat("/a").inode
inode_b_old = as_root.stat("/b").inode

as_root.rename("/a", "/b")

# /b now has /a's old inode and /a's content.
assert as_root.stat("/b").inode == inode_a
fd = as_root.open("/b", flags=0)
assert as_root.read(fd, size=6, offset=0) == b"source"
as_root.close_fd(fd)

# /a is gone. The old /b inode is gone (nlink was 1, no open fds).
assert as_root.exists("/a") is False
```

---

## `test_rename_onto_nonempty_dir_raises(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-rename-5 -->

### Purpose
Renaming over a non-empty directory fails — standard POSIX behavior (ENOTEMPTY or EEXIST depending on the platform; we use `DirectoryNotEmpty`).

### Postconditions

```python
as_root.mkdir("/a")
as_root.mkdir("/b")
fd = as_root.create("/b/inner"); as_root.close_fd(fd)

with pytest.raises(DirectoryNotEmpty):
    as_root.rename("/a", "/b")
# /a still there, /b still there, /b/inner still there.
assert as_root.exists("/a")
assert as_root.exists("/b/inner")
```

---

## `test_rename_onto_empty_dir_succeeds(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-rename-6 -->

### Postconditions

```python
as_root.mkdir("/src", mode=0o700)
as_root.mkdir("/dst", mode=0o755)

as_root.rename("/src", "/dst")
assert as_root.exists("/src") is False
# /dst now has /src's inode and mode.
st = as_root.stat("/dst")
assert st.mode & 0o777 == 0o700
```

---

## `test_rename_into_own_subtree_raises(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-rename-7 -->

### Purpose
Renaming a directory into one of its own descendants would create a cycle. Must be rejected with `FilesystemError` (EINVAL maps to a specific subclass — we use the base `FilesystemError` here since we haven't named an `InvalidArgument` class yet; revisit in errors.engspec).

### Postconditions

```python
as_root.mkdir("/a")
as_root.mkdir("/a/b")
as_root.mkdir("/a/b/c")

with pytest.raises(FilesystemError):
    as_root.rename("/a", "/a/b/c/a")

with pytest.raises(FilesystemError):
    as_root.rename("/a", "/a/b/c")

# Original tree intact.
assert as_root.exists("/a/b/c")
```

---

## `test_rename_src_equals_dst_is_noop(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-rename-8 -->

### Postconditions

```python
fd = as_root.create("/a"); as_root.close_fd(fd)
inode_before = as_root.stat("/a").inode
mtime_before = as_root.stat("/a").mtime_ns

as_root.rename("/a", "/a")

assert as_root.stat("/a").inode == inode_before
# No-op: mtime not bumped.
assert as_root.stat("/a").mtime_ns == mtime_before
```

