## `test_rename_updates_parent_mtimes(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-rename-14 -->

### Purpose
Cross-directory rename bumps mtime on both the source parent and the destination parent. The renamed entry's own mtime is unchanged.

### Postconditions

```python
as_root.mkdir("/src-parent")
as_root.mkdir("/dst-parent")
fd = as_root.create("/src-parent/f"); as_root.close_fd(fd)

src_parent_mtime_before = as_root.stat("/src-parent").mtime_ns
dst_parent_mtime_before = as_root.stat("/dst-parent").mtime_ns
file_mtime_before = as_root.stat("/src-parent/f").mtime_ns

as_root.rename("/src-parent/f", "/dst-parent/f")

assert as_root.stat("/src-parent").mtime_ns > src_parent_mtime_before
assert as_root.stat("/dst-parent").mtime_ns > dst_parent_mtime_before
assert as_root.stat("/dst-parent/f").mtime_ns == file_mtime_before
```

---

## `test_rename_preserves_symlink_target_not_resolved(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-rename-15 -->

### Purpose
Renaming a symlink moves the symlink itself; the target bytes are unchanged. We do NOT follow to resolve-and-copy.

### Postconditions

```python
as_root.symlink(b"/target/does/not/exist", "/link")
as_root.rename("/link", "/relocated")
assert as_root.readlink("/relocated") == b"/target/does/not/exist"
```

---

## `test_rename_atomicity_hint(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-rename-16 -->

### Purpose
A successful `rename` is observable only as "happened completely" — no state where both src and dst exist, or neither does. This test demonstrates the happy path; crash-during-rename atomicity is covered in `test_crash_safety.py.engspec`.

### Postconditions

```python
fd = as_root.create("/src"); as_root.write(fd, b"x", offset=0); as_root.close_fd(fd)

# After rename: exactly one of src/dst exists.
as_root.rename("/src", "/dst")
assert (as_root.exists("/src"), as_root.exists("/dst")) == (False, True)
```

